#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Private Keys in Monero"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/private-key.md:8
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! note\n"
"    Author is nowhere close to being a cryptographer. Be sceptical on accuracy.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/private-key.md:10
#, markdown-text
msgid "In Monero, the root private key is generated [randomly](/cryptography/prng). Other private keys are derived deterministically from the root private key."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/private-key.md:12
#, markdown-text
msgid "Private key must be kept secret."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/private-key.md:15
#, markdown-text
msgid "Private key is a **large integer** impossible to guess, like: `108555083659983933209597798445644913612440610624038028786991485007418559037440`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/private-key.md:17
#, markdown-text
msgid "Private key is 256 bits long."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/private-key.md:19
#, markdown-text
msgid "Private key is a **scalar**, meaning it is a single value."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/private-key.md:21
#, markdown-text
msgid "In equations scalars are represented by **lowercase letters**."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/private-key.md:22
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Relation to Ed25519"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/private-key.md:25
#, markdown-text
msgid "Being simply a random integer, private key is not specific to any particular asymmetric cryptography scheme."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/private-key.md:30
#, markdown-text
msgid "In context of Monero EC cryptography the private key is a number the base point `G` is multiplied by.  The result of the multiplication is the public key `P` (another point on the curve).  Multiplication of a point by a number has a very special definition in EC cryptography.  See this [this guide](https://blog.cloudflare.com/a-relatively-easy-to-understand-primer-on-elliptic-curve-cryptography/) for details."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/private-key.md:31
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Key strength"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/private-key.md:35
#, markdown-text
msgid "Before deriving the public key, private key is subject to modulo `l`, where `l` is the maximum scalar allowed by the [edwards25519 curve](/cryptography/asymmetric/edwards25519)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/private-key.md:38
#, markdown-text
msgid "The `l` is on the order of 2^252, so the effective key strength is technically 252 bits, not 256 bits.  This is standard for EC cryptography and is more of a cosmetic nuance than any concern."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/private-key.md:39
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Encoding"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/private-key.md:42
#, markdown-text
msgid "In user-facing contexts, the private key integer is:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/private-key.md:46
#, markdown-text
msgid "Taken modulo `l` to avoid malleability"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2. '
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/private-key.md:46
#, markdown-text
msgid "Put as array of 32 bytes in a [little-endian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Endianness#Little) direction (the first byte is the least significant)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3. '
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/private-key.md:46
#, markdown-text
msgid "Converted to hexadecimal form, like: `b3588a87056fb21dc4d052d59e83b54293882e646b543c29478e4cf45c28a402`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/private-key.md:47
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Private spend key"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/private-key.md:50
#, markdown-text
msgid "Private spend key is used to spend moneros."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/private-key.md:52
#, markdown-text
msgid "More specifically, it is used to build one-time private keys which allow to spend related outputs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/private-key.md:53
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Private view key"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/private-key.md:56
#, markdown-text
msgid "Private view key is used to recognize your incoming transactions on the otherwise opaque blockchain."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/private-key.md:57
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "One-time private keys"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/private-key.md:59
#, markdown-text
